  "text": "as found in Ref. [CITATION_1] , for example. Where\u00d4 is some general detection operator and the variance squared is given by \u2206\u00d4 2 = \u00d4 2 \u2212 \u00d4 2 . In order to perform such calculations we need to find the first and second moments of the final detection operators. These calculations are straight-forward but extremely lengthy, therefore we created a program in the symbolic calculation software Mathematica TM to perform them, using the NCAlgebra package [32] .",
